    <section class="section" id="about-pcos">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Understanding PCOS</h2>
            <div class="pcos-content">
                <div class="pcos-text">
                    <p><strong>Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS)</strong> is a common hormonal disorder that affects
                        women of reproductive age. It can cause a range of symptoms such as irregular periods, excessive
                        androgen levels (male hormones), and polycystic ovaries. Understanding the condition and taking
                        proactive steps can help in managing its symptoms and long-term effects.</p>

                    <!-- Toggleable Section for Symptoms -->
                    <h3 class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleSection('symptoms')">Symptoms of PCOS <i
                            class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h3>
                    <ul id="symptoms" class="toggle-section">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Irregular menstrual cycles</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Excessive hair growth (hirsutism)</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Weight gain or difficulty losing weight</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Acne and oily skin</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Thinning hair or hair loss</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Infertility or difficulty conceiving</li>
                    </ul>

                    <!-- Toggleable Section for Health Risks -->
                    <h3 class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleSection('health-risks')">Long-term Health Risks <i
                            class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h3>
                    <ul id="health-risks" class="toggle-section">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Type 2 diabetes <span class="tooltip">Caused by
                                insulin resistance associated with PCOS.</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> High blood pressure <span class="tooltip">Linked
                                to obesity and hormonal imbalance.</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Heart disease <span class="tooltip">Higher risk
                                due to metabolic issues.</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Endometrial cancer <span
                                class="tooltip">Resulting from irregular periods and hormonal imbalance.</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="pcos-graphic">
                    <img src="images/PCOS Symptoms.svg" alt="PCOS Overview Graphic">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

